      "writtenOn": "2020-07-14T19:32:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "They\u0027ve removed an item from an already-sorted list using removeShuffle (because SkTArray doesn\u0027t allow erasing from the middle). Almost-perfectly-ordered data is a pathologically bad case for QSort and really efficient for insertion sort. But the \"best\" fix would be for SkTArray to support a proper `erase` method and then no sort would be needed at all.\n\n(In practice I doubt it matters either way since this is probably far off the hot path)",
      "parentUuid": "d91cbc6e_d476b15a",
      "revId": "e6d01aaa81440b832da1a610fb5e68ea2aec70dd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
